==Career==
She started to learn dancing when she was young and started her film career in the parallel cinema when she was 15. Mallika played the role of [[Draupadi]] in the [[Peter Brook]]'s play ''[[The Mahabharata (1989 film)|The Mahabharata]]''. Mallika has won many accolades during her long career, the Golden Star Award is one of them, which she won for the Best Dance Soloist, Theatre De Champs Elysees, Paris 1977. As well as a dancer, Sarabhai is a social activist.<ref>[http://www.womensweb.in/articles/inspiring-woman-mallika-sarabhai/ Inspiring woman ]</ref> She manages the [[Darpana Academy of Performing Arts]] located at Ahmedabad, a centre for the arts and for the use of arts as a language for behaviour change.<ref>[http://www.darpana.com/about_us_mallika_sarabhai.php Welcome to the world of Darpana] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719072652/http://www.darpana.com/about_us_mallika_sarabhai.php |date=19 July 2011 }}</ref>

